  <!-- ===== NARRATIVE ===== -->
  <section class="narrative" aria-labelledby="why-heading">
    <h2 id="why-heading">Why this exists</h2>
    <p>Stakeholders engaged in traffic safety across the City and region noticed a significant rise in aggressive driving, serious injury crashes, and traffic fatalities over the past few years. To combat these trends, the City applied and acquired funds through the federal Safe Streets for All grant program — a federally-funded program designed to reduce deaths and serious injuries using the <strong>Safe System Approach</strong>.</p>
    <p>The Colorado Springs Safety Action Plan outlines five systemic improvements and specific projects to reduce serious and deadly crashes. The data behind the plan is published as a public ArcGIS feature service — the same feed used by the City&rsquo;s own dashboard. Our <a href="/microsites/city/traffic/SafetyPlan/cos-traffic-hub.html" style="color:#ffd577;">Traffic Safety Dashboard</a> consumes that same feed in a fully accessible interface, with zip-code search, exportable records, and screen-reader friendly chart fallbacks.</p>
    <p><em>None of the data behind this plan was secret. It just wasn&rsquo;t in a form residents could use.</em></p>
